sentences: Huw Evans (born 15 March 1985), also known as H. Hawkline, is a Welsh singer-songwriter and radio and television presenter based in Cardiff.
Hywel Gwynfryn and his wife Anja (who died in 2018)
He also presented a weekly radio show on the C2 evening slot on BBC Radio Cymru until summer 2012.
In December 2015 he temporarily returned to the station to present a Thursday-night show.
H. Hawkline's debut release, the album A Cup of Salt, was put out in 2010 by the then-Cardiff-based label Shape Records.
His second album, The Strange Uses of Ox Gall, was released by the same label in 2011.
He supported Gruff Rhys on tour in 2010 in the UK and Ireland.
Following UK festival gigs and touring, in 2012 H. Hawkline released a new EP, Black Domino Box, on the Trash Aesthetics label.
His Ghouls EP was released in 2013 by Turnstile Records.
In 2013, H. Hawkline moved to Los Angeles with his then-partner Cate Le Bon, and there the two continue to collaborate musically.
In August 2014, H. Hawkline was signed to Heavenly Recordings.
His debut album of new material for the label, In the Pink of Condition, was released in February 2015.
In September 2015, the album was nominated for the 2014-2015 Welsh Music Prize.
In 2017, H. Hawkline supported Devendra Banhart on tour in the US and Europe/UK, followed by a European support slot with Aldous Harding, whom he also played with during her headline set.
His next album I Romanticize was released in June 2017 on Heavenly.
Evans continues to perform as part of then-partner's Aldous Harding band, and appeared on her 2019 album Designer playing bass, guitar and keys.

Salt Gall Box Ghouls (best-of, August 2014, Heavenly Recordings)
As a solo artist, he supported Foxygen on their 2015 European tour.
Prior to becoming a full-time musician, Evans presented the S4C music show Bandit with Huw Stephens up to the show's cancellation at the end of 2011.
